## Vercel Speed Insights Installation Complete

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Vite + React project.

### Changes Made:

**1. Package Installation:**
   - Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package (version added to dependencies)
   - Updated package.json and package-lock.json

**2. Code Integration (src/App.tsx):**
   - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/react";`
   - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the BrowserRouter, following React best practices
   - Component placed after Routes to ensure it's loaded on all pages

**3. Verification:**
   - Build completed successfully (npm run build)
   - No new linting errors introduced in modified files
   - SpeedInsights component follows framework-specific instructions from official Vercel documentation

### Implementation Details:

Following the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), I used the React-specific integration method:
- Used `@vercel/speed-insights/react` import (React/Vite projects)
- Placed component at the application root level within App.tsx
- Component will automatically collect and send performance metrics to Vercel

### Next Steps:

To complete the Speed Insights setup:
1. Deploy this change to Vercel
2. Enable Speed Insights in your Vercel project dashboard
3. Performance data will start appearing in your dashboard after deployment

### Files Modified:
- package.json (added dependency)
- package-lock.json (updated with new package)
- src/App.tsx (added SpeedInsights component)
